it’s always a good day to bring women together 🥰

My choreography is usually constructed through blending different parts/sounds of the music together based on what I gravitate towards. But for this, I wanted to put myself in a producer’s shoes and separate different musical groups (main vocals, beats, & background/adlibs) to compose a piece with separate moving parts, all working together cohesively.

I was so close to canceling this shoot - self doubt and resistance were verrryyyy present during this process of investing in my work again. If you’ve been having trouble believing that your ideas are worth executing, this is your sign to just make that shit!!❤️‍🔥 it doesn’t always have to be that deep, you really CAN just create because you enjoy it, no matter the outcome. Here’s to more showing up for ourselves and more creating — not for the sake of releasing more final products, but for the sake of exploring what we have within us.

home from a 2 week trip to celebrate our wedding with John’s family in Taiwan, and also for a lil round 2 of our honeymoon in Japan :) trying to travel as much as we can before we decide to expand our family hehe. These pics/videos are my favorite because they represent how our love shows up the strongest in the quiet, in-between moments of life together: like John patiently disassembling a round brush that was completely stuck in my head in order to save my hair 😃 - running to get me medicine, hot soup, tea, and massaging away my migraine when I started to feel sick - and just so many other moments not captured. Bickering and making up, infinite grace for each other, infinite patience on Johns end 😬, infinite laughter and geeking out over good food, and the depths of care and attention shown constantly. In every lifetime I hope to experience our love over and over again. 🤍
Had to squeeze in just one class while I was in Japan. Dancing with my girls 😭❤️‍🔥 I’ve missed y’all so much!!!!!!! I’ll teach a round of this soon in LA 👀

THE CHOREOGRAPHY MENTORSHIP + LIVE SHOWCASE! My goal isn’t to make you create or look like me, my goal is to facilitate a space where your own choreography practice is expanded and encouraged through guided exercises, creative tasks, studying film, lectures/discussions, and personal feedback. If you’re serious about committing, send an email to info@sorahyang.com for full details and application! ***Only taking 12 students so I can give individual care and attention to each participant*** This program is catered to the int/adv pre-professional level. Applicants must be 18yrs+ based in SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA / able to travel to LA for all program dates.
THE CHOREOGRAPHY MENTORSHIP + LIVE SHOWCASE **applications closed!** | Will absolutely do more of these in the future ☺️

[ Muse-icality ] I wanted to expand on my last concept by approaching it in a new way — allowing the movement alone to deliver the idea (no colored lighting, no separate frames). Working with these two @amvndamay @macyswaimyy was a dream, truly the ultimate muses and the definition of movement quality in my eyes. Had to fight off some imposter syndrome and fatigue to get this one done but we did it baby😅! Nothing is better for your confidence than following through. Hope you enjoy the viewing/listening experience 🫶🏼 (watch til the very end of you wanna know what it was really like filming this lol)

GOOD TIMES 2023. My piece was a celebration of female unity, because it’s something I’ve always wanted to see and feel more of in our community. EMPOWERED WOMEN EMPOWER WOMEN. Uplifting and supporting other women (with the same enthusiasm we are willing to give to men) is an act of self love, and doing the opposite only holds us all back. I want young girls watching this to feel encouraged to build with each other, the women around me to remember that we’re all in this together, and the women who came before us to know that we would not be here without them. 💐 

A HUGE thank you to my cast of kind, talented, badass women, as well as ALL the ladies from teams around the community who joined me on stage to create this moment with us.💖 To the brilliant @arianaelizshenlee for opening my set with spoken word — it was an honor to have you. To @companyfam, thank you for your leadership in cultivating community and for always providing a platform for my voice.🙏🏼

More clips to come eventually, but for now the full performance footage can be found on YouTube courtesy of @vibrvncy @geraldnonadoez :)

heart is still here 🥹 what an honor and joy it was to connect with and guide these artists over the past few weeks ❤️ beyond the mentorship elements, the core purpose of this program is really simple: to remind people that their creative expression/individuality is worthy of existing, nurturing, and taking up space. Excited to continue to run this program whenever I have the time and capacity 🫶🏼 it really fills my heart up!!!

still here, still creating, still trying, still growing, still going. 🤍

It doesn’t matter how many followers you have - IG makes a lot of artists feel like shit. I understand that these feelings are common but I’m also committed to not letting numbers discourage me from continuing to create and share, and also not being motivated by them in any way either. I’m rebelling against my own uncertainties of “am I enough” and “is there really space for me in this crowded dance world with so much epic talent” and “does anyone even care” by simply choosing to keep going. In a world hyper-fixated on being the best, remember that no one can beat you at being yourself.

Come grow with me weekly 🥹💚 (starting NEXT WEEK 9/13). mL means so much to me - a place that formed some of my favorite dance memories both as a teacher and a student and connected me with lifelong friendships. Trying out a weekly (!!!) class with the intention of building COMMUNITY and CONSISTENCY for those seeking it. My classes have always felt like a melting pot of dance backgrounds and generations from all over the world and I hope it continues to feel that way moving forward - a place where we can all come together for a shared love of movement no matter where you come from. I’m honored, excited, and can’t wait to make some new favorite memories 💚💚💚 WEDNESDAYS @ 7:30 JUST GOT SPICIER 🌶 let’s get it!!!!!

Choreo Mentorship Vol 2 - Showcase Recap

- 13 hours of group sessions over 3-4 days (lectures, discussion, film study, creative exercises, prompts)

✨ Private Session Student Spotlight: @karaskye__ ✨
Kara already walked into the session having gotten the class combo down well, so we focused on increasing her dynamic range (more contrast in movement), connecting more deeply with her performance/expression, and gaining more confidence in her ability to execute the fast moments. She did AMAAZING! Just look at that end of session take 😍

These private group sessions are meant to take a class combo and actually use it to train, rather than just memorize new steps every week and never practice them again. They’re paired with my Wed night classes at mL as an extended space to connect more deeply and grow more intentionally for those seeking direct feedback and guidance. Keep an eye out for the next one (usually announced on my stories or in class)🤍
